reviewText: I bought this as part of the Mighty Morphin to Lost Galaxy megaset last year.  But I imagine it stands up well enough on its own if you're purchasing the series a volume at a time.  This set contains some pretty amazing episodes.  We start it off with the explosive introduction of Lord Zedd in the 3 part season premier, The Mutiny.  Fans can also relive Tommy's last days as the Green Ranger as Zedd begins to target him specifically.  Tommy takes his final stand in the 2 part miniseries Green No more, but one of the best moments in MMPR history is still to come in the White Light 2 parter which is also included here.  Other reviewers have posted episode lists but I'll go ahead and provide one if mine was the first you happened upon. I'm still a bit confused when it comes to the chronological order of a few of these so i'd appreciate any comments pertaining to chronological order.  Well nostalgic comments are fun too so go nuts.  Anyway, here's what you'll get in this volume.61.  The Mutiny, part 162.  The Mutiny, Part 263.  The Mutiny, part 364.  The Wanna-Be Ranger65.  Putty On The Brain66.  Bloom of Doom67.  The Green Dream(I wanna say this one was aired out of order.  Tommy makes a comment about Zedd having it in for him since the beginning but he hasn't even begun to target Tommy yet.  More on that later.)68.  The Power Stealer(Fox Kids used to air this one before all the other Green Rangercentric episodes in season 2 during reruns.69.  The Beetle Invasion70.  Welcome to Venus Island71.  The Song of Guitardo72.  Green No More, part 173.  Green No More, part 274.  Missing Green75.  Orchestral Maneuvers in the Park76.  Beauty and the Beast77.  White Light, part 178.  White Light, part 2(Watched these two when they first aired and they're still just as awesome.)79.  Two for One80.  Opposites Attract81.  Zedd's Monster Mash82.  The Ninja Encounter, part 183.  The Ninja Encounter, part 284.  The Ninja Encounter, part 385.  A Monster of Global Proportions86.  Zedd WavesAs stated above, still unsure of the Green Ranger arc, but most episode guides I've read online state that they should be viewed as follows. And this is the way I remember Fox Kids reairing them.  The Power Stealer, The Beetle Invasion, Welcome to Venus Island, The Green Dream, The Song of Guitardo, and Green No More parts 1 and 2.  I want to say the rest of the episodes on these discs are in chronological order.  So I think we're all good there.These releases of MMPR are terrific.  They're great for long time fans as well as a treat for new generations to come.  Please don't pass these up.  Go ahead and nab them while the nabbing's good.  $15 or so for 26 episodes and all that jazz.  You can't beat that price.

reviewText: While White Ranger is posed in the center, Tommy Oliver still has his Green Ranger power for a good chunk of this Volume. The Green No More and White Light 2 part episodes are in this volume, Essentially the fall of the Green Ranger and the rise of the White Ranger to become the official leader of the Power Rangers, leaving Red Ranger to be a supporting role, as the actor didn't return for some reason to next season.
